Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addNetToNetGroup(25.10)                                addNetToNetGroup(25.10)

Name
       addNetToNetGroup  -  Adds a net to specified net group that was created
       with the createNetGroup command

Syntax
       addNetToNetGroup

       [-help]

       netGroupName

       -net {<netName> | <netNameList>}

       Adds a net to specified net group that was created with the  createNet-
       Group  command.  A  net  can be a single net, bus name, or segment of a
       bus. You can use this command after defining a net group.

       Note: If a net is a part of a net group, the net cannot belong  to  any
       other net group.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each addNetToNetGroup parameter. For a  detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command: man addNetToNetGroup

       <netGroupName>
              Specifies the name of the created net group.

              Data_type: string, required

       -net {<netName> | <netNameList>}
              Specifies the name of an individual net, bus, or  segment  of  a
              bus. You can use wildcards (*?) with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, required

Examples
              * The following command adds net ENOUT to net group bundle1:

                addNetToNetGroup bundle1 -net ENOUT

              * The  following  command  adds the entire bus cpua to net group
                bundle2:

                addNetToNetGroup bundle2 -net cpua

              * The following command adds only bus segments 2 through  10  to
                net group bundle1:

                addNetToNetGroup bundle1 -net cpua[2:10]

